def originaldigits(s: str) -> str:
    from collections import Counter
    count = Counter(s)
    res = dict()
    res[0] = count['z']
    res[2] = count['w']
    res[4] = count['u']
    res[6] = count['x']
    res[8] = count['g']
    res[3] = count['h'] + res[8]
    res[5] = count['f'] - res[4]
    res[7] = count['v'] - res[5]
    res[1] = count['o'] - res[0] - res[2] - res[4]
    res[9] = count['i'] - res[5] - res[6] - res[8]
    result = [str(i) * num for (i, num) in sorted(res.items())]
    return ''.join(result)
